text: I would like to talk about my choices for my studies. Firstly, to explain, and then you should understand my choice, I have a sister who's 3 years older than me. In college or High school, teachers already had an image from me by my sister, and that's could be pretty bad or good. In my case, it was pretty bad cause I was the exact opposite of my sister. She was a really good student, studying every days, and that's obviously not my case. So I did a S baccalaureat, exactly like my sister cause I don't really known what i wanted to do. I was in Sport Option cause I love sport. At the half of the last year of High School, we have to actually decide what we want to do for our future but it's a really hard choice. I randomly put Schools on my ParcourSup, like Staps( because I love sport obviously), and I also put ESIR because my sister was actually doing the "matériaux" cursus. She was talking of the informatic cursus to me and she was like "ye you can like it", so I decided to put ESIR as my first choice. I also went to the Student Saloon, and I talked with some students from the Staps cursus. They explained me the different subjects and I was not interessed at all in every subject except the Sport, but even in the Sport subject, teachers were chosing the sports. So after this Student Saloon, I definitely wanted to don't go to Staps. During the Sallon, i met some people from other schools or IUT or what ever, but I was not interested anymore after a discussion with them. So I put my devolute on ESIR and I did the "prépa intégré" and then I joined the school. But now, I have actually no idea for what I want to do after my studies. It's not like i'm not liking Informatic but i'm not liking that that much so i'm in a dubitative mood. I don't really know what to do after ESIR, but I have 2 years to find so it's fine. In ESIR 3, I will try to go to a neighbor country in Stage or for a semester and it can may be open my eyes on something or open my mind.
